abstract: In the waning hours before New Hampshire’s first-in-the-nation primary voting begins, Democratic presidential candidates took varied approaches to the expectations game Monday as they look to advance deeper into what could be an extended nominating fight.

abstract: New Hampshire voters are poised Tuesday to re-order the field of Democratic presidential candidates. But as important, they will also send a message about what kind of change they want their party to stand for to challenge President Donald Trump.

lead_paragraph: HANOVER, N.H. — New Hampshire voters are poised Tuesday to re-order the field of Democratic presidential candidates. But as important, they will also send a message about what kind of change they want their party to stand for to challenge President Donald Trump.
headline_main: Revolution or Realism? NH Tests Democrats' Call for Change

abstract: U.S. Attorney General William Barr on Monday confirmed that the Justice Department has received information from President Donald Trump's personal lawyer Rudy Giuliani ahead of the November election, but that anything originating from Ukraine should not be taken "at face value."

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. Attorney General William Barr on Monday confirmed that the Justice Department has received information from President Donald Trump's personal lawyer Rudy Giuliani ahead of the November election, but that anything originating from Ukraine should not be taken "at face value."
headline_main: Barr: U.S. Scrutinizing Information Ahead of 2020 Election, Including From Giuliani

abstract: For Jeff Sessions, Roy Moore and other Republicans vying for a chance to take back Doug Jones’s seat, winning over voters may mean winning over the president first.
snippet: For Jeff Sessions, Roy Moore and other Republicans vying for a chance to take back Doug Jones’s seat, winning over voters may mean winning over the president first.
lead_paragraph: In early November, President Trump announced he would be traveling to Tuscaloosa, Ala., to attend the University of Alabama-Louisiana State University football game. When Representative Bradley Byrne, a three-term congressman and United States Senate candidate from Mobile, learned of this plan, he immediately called an Alabama booster named Jim Wilson, who would be hosting Trump in his luxury box near midfield at Bryant-Denny Stadium. Wilson, as fortune would have it, is a distant relative, friend and financial supporter of Byrne’s, and Byrne thought perhaps he could get him into the box.

abstract: A day before New Hampshire votes in its Democratic presidential primary, Bernie Sanders and Pete Buttigieg sought on Monday to build on their strength as front-runners in an up-for-grabs race as an energized Senator Amy Klobuchar gained ground.
snippet: A day before New Hampshire votes in its Democratic presidential primary, Bernie Sanders and Pete Buttigieg sought on Monday to build on their strength as front-runners in an up-for-grabs race as an energized Senator Amy Klobuchar gained ground....
lead_paragraph: KEENE/NASHUA, N.H. — A day before New Hampshire votes in its Democratic presidential primary, Bernie Sanders and Pete Buttigieg sought on Monday to build on their strength as front-runners in an up-for-grabs race as an energized Senator Amy Klobuchar gained ground.
headline_main: On Eve of New Hampshire Democratic Vote, Klobuchar Gains Ground on Sanders and Buttigieg
headline_print_headline: On Eve of New Hampshire Democratic Vote, Klobuchar Gains Ground on Sanders and Buttigieg

abstract: For the past year, Democratic voters have been anxious to settle on a savior capable of defeating President Donald Trump.
snippet: For the past year, Democratic voters have been anxious to settle on a savior capable of defeating President Donald Trump.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, New Hampshire — For the past year, Democratic voters have been anxious to settle on a savior capable of defeating President Donald Trump.
headline_main: Democrats in Disarray in New Hampshire as Sanders Surges and Trump Provokes
headline_print_headline: Democrats in Disarray in New Hampshire as Sanders Surges and Trump Provokes

abstract: As Bong Joon Ho’s film received Academy Awards for best picture and best director, the honors set off cheers and a burst of pride in a country fearful of being overlooked.
snippet: As Bong Joon Ho’s film received Academy Awards for best picture and best director, the honors set off cheers and a burst of pride in a country fearful of being overlooked.
lead_paragraph: SEOUL, South Korea — Much of the world knows South Korea by its cultural products, including its increasingly popular movies, TV dramas and K-pop performers like BTS and Psy. Now the country has received once-unthinkable validation of its artistic achievement: a best-picture Oscar.
